<concept xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="topic_6_1">
   <title id="title_a11">Creating a Chart</title>
   <conbody>
    <p>IMPORTANT: Before you begin creating and configuring a chart:</p>
    <ul id="ul_g5s_r4q_zx">
      <li>
        <p>Be sure you have run its corresponding report. This way the system has already verified
          the datatypes of each field in the reporting results, giving you the opportunity to review
          the results and decide which fields are best to use in the chart.</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Be sure your system meets the requirements noted in Appendix ???? if you are creating a
          custom chart.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p>To create a chart for a corresponding report, you can use one of the following two methods
      listed below.</p>
   <ol> <li>To run the report and add the chart from the report results view<ol><li>Go to the Analyzer dashboard, select Data Design from the dropdown list and click Reports.<p>The
              Manage Report screen with the current listing of reports is displayed. </p></li><li>Scroll or find the desired report, check the report, and click Run.</li><li>From the view results screen for the report, click the Gear icon, and choose Add a Chart from
            the dropdown list.</li><li>Go to Step 3.<p>Figure 5-1: Add a Chart</p><p><image href="./media/Image_210.jpg" height="172"
                width="390" id="image_npj_s4q_zx"/></p></li></ol></li>
    <li>Add the chart from Edit Report definition screen:<ol><li>Go to the Analyzer dashboard, select Data Design from the dropdown list and click Reports.<p>The
              Manage Report screen with the current listing of reports is displayed.</p></li><li>Scroll or find the desired report, check mark the report that requires the chart, and click
              Edit.<p>Figure 5-2: Select Report for the Chart.</p><p><image
                href="./media/Image_211.jpg" height="320" width="560" id="image_opj_s4q_zx"
              /></p><p>The Database Table Report Settings screen to define the report is
              displayed.</p><p>Figure 5-3: Database Table Report Settings Screen</p><p><image
                href="./media/Image_212.jpg" height="333" width="612" id="image_ppj_s4q_zx"
            /></p></li></ol></li>
    <li>Click the Charting tab and select a chart type from the dropdown list; then click Add to
        bring up the applicable chart type configuration box to create the chart.<p>Figure 5-4:
          Charting Tab</p><p><image href="./media/Image_213.jpg" height="332" width="370"
            id="image_qpj_s4q_zx"/></p><p>
          <note>NOTE: Chart types include: Area Chart, Bar Chart, Location Map, Heatmap, Pie Chart,
            and Trending Chart.</note>
        </p></li>
      <li>Go to the relevant section of this chapter for details on providing chart information for
        your specified chart type:<ul id="ul_rpj_s4q_zx">
          <li>
            <p><xref href="c_sen_anal-6_3-Creating-or-Modifyin_crm.xml"/></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><xref href="c_sen_anal-6_4-Creating-or-Modifyin_crm.xml"/></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><xref href="c_sen_anal-6_5-Creating-or-Modifyin_crm.xml"/></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><xref href="c_sen_anal-6_6-Creating-or-Modifyin_crm.xml"/></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><xref href="c_sen_anal-6_7-Creating-or-Modifyin_crm.xml"/></p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><xref href="c_sen_anal-6_8-Creating-or-Modifyin_crm.xml"/></p>
          </li>
        </ul><p>After you have created and saved a chart, you can modify it. See Editing a Chart
          below.</p></li></ol>
  </conbody>
</concept>
